THEATRE company, Ibadan Playhouse has set out plans to stage Wole Soyinka’s ‘Trials Of Brother Jero’ on Sunday, August 26, 2018. Speaking to The Nation, Ropo Ewenla, of Ibadan Playhouse said that the play will be staged at the Little Theatre of Lagos Country Club, Ikeja, Lagos. According to him, Lagos-based theatre group, Crown Troupe of Africa will interpret the play. As a way of bringing back the theatre culture, Lagos Country Club in recent times have played host to theatre performances. 